<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>



<p>If there’s one thing worse than neglecting your thank you page, it’s overusing it.</p>



<p>I’ve outlined above nine of the best thank you page best practices available—but you need to be selective.</p>



<p>Don’t overwhelm your new subscriber with requests to refer a friend, follow you on Twitter, complete a survey, etc. Instead, focus on one best practice, test it, and iterate as needed.</p>



<p><em>How do you use your thank you page? Leave a comment below.</em></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/thank-you-page">9 Essential Elements of a High-Converting Thank You Page (+ Examples)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://sleeknote.com">Sleeknote</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
