										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center"><strong>Harry’s Marketing: What We Learned from Reverse Engineering a $400 Million Startup (Case Study)</strong></h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/growth-marketing" rel="category tag">Growth Marketing</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="437" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-1024x437.jpg" alt="Harry’s Marketing [WordPress]" class="wp-image-79225" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-1024x437.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-300x128.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-768x328.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-1536x656.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-380x162.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-600x256.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-760x325.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-1440x615.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-960x410.jpg 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-740x316.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress-385x164.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Harry’s-Marketing-WordPress.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_5e7ca1c4b137e" class="block-preamble"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ever heard of </span><a href="https://www.harrys.com/en/us" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Harry’s</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">? Since founding the company in 2013, co-founders Jeff Raider and Andy Katz-Mayfield have turned their shaving subscription service into a global online powerhouse.</span></p>
</div>






<p>And the numbers don’t lie:<br></p>



<ul><li>$250 million in venture capital (<a href="https://www.inc.com/magazine/201605/bernhard-warner/harrys-razors-german-factory.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Inc.</a>)</li><li>$200 million in revenue in 2017 alone (<a href="http://www.adweek.com/creativity/harrys-shaving-brand-tells-its-whole-unlikely-story-fun-long-form-ad-175335/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Adweek</a>)</li><li>3 million monthly recurring customers and counting (<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/harry%27s-grooming/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">LinkedIn</a>)</li></ul>



<p>But what’s most interesting, and what I want to focus your attention on, is their marketing strategy. Not because it’s anything new. But rather, because it’s applicable to any e-commerce store, regardless of size.<br></p>



<p>I recently spent a month reverse-engineering Harry&#8217;s marketing strategy and today, <strong>I want to show you five battle-tested strategies you can use to get more engagement and higher conversions.</strong>&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>The best part? They work even if you don’t have venture capital or a multi-million dollar marketing budget.<br></p>



<p>Sound good?<br></p>



<p>Let’s get started.<br></p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e7ca238b137f" class="block-content-upgrade">
    <div class="text">
        <p class="text-pretitle"></p>
        <h2 class="text-title">Download Harry’s Marketing Toolkit</h2>
        <div class="text-content"><p>This article took 20 hours to write. Twenty. Needless to say, there was a LOT I couldn’t include in the post. To make life easier, I’ve compiled a swipe file of Harry’s marketing materials. Plus, a few extra goodies (*cough* a bonus strategy that’s too good to ignore).</p>
<p>Get access to Harry’s Marketing toolkit and get more traffic and higher engagement today (includes bonus content not included in the post, email examples, Facebook ads, and more).</p>
