<h2><strong>11 of The Best Email Marketing Examples We’ve Ever Seen</strong></h2>



<p><a href="#1">1. The Welcome Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#2">2. The Curation Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#3">3. The Engagement Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#4">4. The Referral Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#5">5. The Discount Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#6">6. The Cart Abandonment Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#7">7. The Order Confirmation Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#8">8. The Upsell Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#9">9. The Win-Back Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#10">10. The Survey Email</a></p>



<p><a href="#11">11. The Thank You Email</a></p>





<h2 id="1"><strong>1. The Welcome Email</strong></h2>



<p>You have one chance to make a good first impression. And if your introduction to a new subscriber isn’t memorable, your follow-up campaigns won’t be, either.</p>



<p>Driving <a href="https://www.experian.com/assets/marketing-services/reports/welcome-best-practices-guide.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">3 times the transaction and revenue</a> per email than any other promotional mailing, the welcome email is an integral campaign in your repertoire.</p>



<p>Its role is to thank subscribers for joining your list, set expectations for what’s to come (e.g. how often you’ll email) and, when done right, simplify your sales process.</p>



<p><a href="https://us.pandora.net/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Pandora</a>, for example, rewards new subscribers for signing up by offering a discount code:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="900" height="560" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email.png" alt="Pandora Welcome Email" class="wp-image-91976" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email.png 900w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-300x187.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-768x478.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-380x236.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-600x373.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-760x473.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-56x35.png 56w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-80x50.png 80w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-740x460.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-220x137.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pandora-Welcome-Email-385x240.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></figure></div>



<p><a href="https://www.levi.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Levi’s</a>, another retailer that realizes the importance of a good welcome email, gives their subscribers the chance to browse by buying preference:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="960" height="290" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email.png" alt="Levi_s Welcome Email" class="wp-image-91968" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email.png 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-300x91.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-768x232.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-380x115.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-600x181.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-760x230.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-116x35.png 116w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-166x50.png 166w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-740x224.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-220x66.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Levi_s-Welcome-Email-385x116.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></figure></div>



<p>A few things to consider:</p>



<ul><li><strong>Aim for originality.</strong> If you want to rise above the noise in your audience’s inbox, you need to be original. And that means doing something that subscribers aren’t expecting. Offer a discount. Speak their language. Tell them to reply to your email. Give them everything they need to inform them that they’re in the right place.</li></ul>



<ul><li><strong>Design for simplicity.</strong> If you have a big product range, remove barriers for making purchases. Whether that’s by product category or something else, make it easy for new subscribers to browse what they’re looking for.</li></ul>





<h2 id="2"><strong>2. The Curation Email</strong></h2>



<p><em>One</em> by The Beatles. <em>The Immaculate Collection</em> by Madonna. <em>Gold: Greatest Hits</em> by Abba.</p>



<p>What do they all have in common?</p>



<p>(Apart from being best of compilations?)</p>



<p><em>They’re some of the best-selling albums of all-time.</em></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="268" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-1024x268.png" alt="Best-Selling Albums of All Time" class="wp-image-91920" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-1024x268.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-300x79.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-768x201.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-380x100.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-600x157.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-760x199.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-134x35.png 134w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-191x50.png 191w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-740x194.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-220x58.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time-385x101.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Best-Selling-Albums-of-All-Time.png 1335w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Why?</p>



<p><em>Because people LOVE curated content.</em></p>



<p>It doesn’t matter whether it’s music—or, in our case, physical products—people love buying the best of the best.</p>



<p>It’s no surprise, then, that the curation email is popular among e-commerce marketers.</p>



<p>If you’re unfamiliar, the goal, with the curation email, is to share a brand’s best assets.</p>



<p>That might be sharing popular content from a previous week, like <a href="https://www.onekingslane.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">One King’s Lane</a> does:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="750" height="600" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email.png" alt="One King Lane Curation Email" class="wp-image-91972" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email.png 750w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-300x240.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-380x304.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-600x480.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-44x35.png 44w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-63x50.png 63w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-613x490.png 613w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-220x176.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/One-King-Lane-Curation-Email-385x308.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /></figure></div>



<p>Or, promoting popular products, as <a href="https://huckberry.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Huckberry</a> does in their email:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="499" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-1024x499.png" alt="3 Must-Have Bike Tools" class="wp-image-91896" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-1024x499.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-300x146.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-768x374.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-380x185.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-600x292.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-760x370.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-72x35.png 72w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-103x50.png 103w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-740x361.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-220x107.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools-385x188.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/3-Must-Have-Bike-Tools.png 1190w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Curating the best of the best works because it allows subscribers to choose what they want to learn more about.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It’s why many websites have “start here” pages, and why <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/product-page-examples" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">product pages</a> are often filtered by bestselling by default.</p>



<p>But there’s another reason why it’s effective:&nbsp;</p>



<p><em>It allows email marketers to segment recipients based on interest.&nbsp;</em></p>



<p>Here’s an example:</p>



<p>Imagine you’re running an online furniture store and your newsletter curates the best furniture under the following categories:</p>



<ol><li>Seating</li><li>Lighting</li><li>Storage cabinets</li><li>Decorative objects</li><li>Tables</li><li>Serveware</li><li>Other</li></ol>



<p>If you’re tagging subscribers using an email service provider (ESP) like <a href="https://www.infusionsoft.com/">Infusionsoft</a>, you can begin scoring them based on their behavior. For example, if a user ONLY clicks seating-related promotions, it’s safe to assume that you can focus your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/promotional-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">promotional campaigns</a> related ONLY to seating.</p>





<h2 id="3"><strong>3. The Engagement Email</strong></h2>



<p>Back in the golden age of direct response marketing, copywriter Gary Halbert was famous for attaching “grabbers” like dollar bills to mailings.</p>



<p>Why?&nbsp;</p>



<p><em>Because he needed to get his prospects’ attention.</em>&nbsp;</p>



<p>With the average office worker receiving as many as <a href="http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">122 emails per day</a>, it’s crucial you invite subscribers to engage with your emails if you stay visible in their inbox.</p>



<p>While attaching cryptocurrency to campaigns might not be a viable option, it is possible to increase engagement in other ways (and without breaking the bank).</p>



<p><a href="https://www.brooklinen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Brooklinen</a>, for example, encourages engagement by offering free shipping:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="670" height="570" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email.png" alt="Brooklinen Engagement Email" class="wp-image-91932" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email.png 670w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-300x255.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-380x323.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-600x510.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-41x35.png 41w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-59x50.png 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-576x490.png 576w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-220x187.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Engagement-Email-385x328.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /></figure></div>



<p>Brooklinen knows that shipping is a common reason for cart abandonment. So, not only do they offer free shipping to subscribers, but they also give them a way to <em>activate</em> it. And it’s clever. Brooklinen knows that people value things they have to work for &#8230; and getting free shipping is no exception.</p>



<p>Campaigns like the above not only encourage engagement; it also builds a two-way relationship between Brooklinen and their customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>So, whether you’re offering free shipping or inviting users to <a href="https://sleeknote.com/start-free-trial" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">start a free trial</a>, give readers a reason to engage with your campaigns and remember, make it memorable.&nbsp;</p>





<h2 id="4"><strong>4. The Referral Email</strong></h2>



<p>It’s no secret that inviting customers to refer friends and family to a brand is a great source for free leads.</p>



<p>According to <a href="http://www.ogilvy.com/News/Press-Releases/June-2014-Consumer-behavior-comes-under-the-spotlight-in-new-study.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">a recent survey by BigCommerce</a>, <strong>74% of consumers identify word-of-mouth as a key influencer in their purchasing decision.</strong></p>



<p>And with numbers like that, it’s not hard to see why brands invest time in setting up good referral programs.</p>



<p>You might already be asking for referrals on your <a href="http://www.sleeknote.com/blog/thank-you-page" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">thank you page</a> (and if you’re not, you ought to be). But are you doing it in your email campaigns, too?</p>



<p><a href="https://bombas.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Bombas</a> is a good illustration of asking for referrals. Not only do they give clear instructions in their email, but they also offer an incentive: a free pair of socks:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="555" height="575" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email.png" alt="Bombas Referral Email" class="wp-image-91928" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email.png 555w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-290x300.png 290w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-380x394.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-34x35.png 34w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-48x50.png 48w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-473x490.png 473w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-220x228.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Referral-Email-385x399.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px" /></figure></div>



<p>You might not be able to offer free socks with each referral (few can), but you certainly have enough money in your marketing budget to offer a thank you (or at least an Internet high five).</p>





<h2 id="5"><strong>5. The Discount Email</strong></h2>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/discount-strategy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Discounting</a> is an effective <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-marketing-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">e-commerce marketing strategy</a>.</p>



<p>And with brands like <a href="https://sleeknote.com/success-stories/apuls" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Apuls</a> getting conversion rates as high as <strong>5.13%</strong>, it’s not hard to see why.</p>



<p><a href="http://cdn2.hubspot.net/hub/310840/file-2031207983-pdf/VWO_ecommerce_report_new.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">One study by VWO</a> found that 72% of Millennial shoppers are open to retargeting via discounts.</p>



<p>Moreover, 54% of shoppers are likely to purchase abandoned products if they’re offered again at a discounted price. (More on that shortly).</p>



<p><a href="https://www.blueapron.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Blue Apron</a>, an American meal delivery service, regularly offer discounts to their subscribers to entice more purchases (note the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/scarcity-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">scarcity</a> to evoke the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/fomo-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">fear of missing out</a>):&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="544" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-1024x544.png" alt="Blue Apron Discount Email" class="wp-image-91924" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-1024x544.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-300x159.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-768x408.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-380x202.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-600x319.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-760x404.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-66x35.png 66w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-94x50.png 94w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-740x393.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-220x117.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email-385x205.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Discount-Email.png 1110w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Be warned, though:</p>



<p>While discounting is effective, you need to strike a balance.</p>



<p>Too often and your profits will plummet; too little and you risk driving customers to a competitor.</p>



<p>The silver lining, then, is to offer discounts to ONLY subscribers that engage with your campaigns (e.g. opening emails, clicking links, etc.).</p>





<h2 id="6"><strong>6. The Cart Abandonment Email</strong></h2>



<p>We’ve all done it.</p>



<p>We’re online, going through a website’s checkout, when <em>something</em> diverts our attention.</p>



<p>There’s a knock on the door, we get a Facebook notification, our phone rings…</p>



<p>And we abandoned our cart without batting an eyelid.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="810" height="341" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart.png" alt="I_ve Abandoned My Cart" class="wp-image-91964" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart.png 810w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-300x126.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-768x323.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-380x160.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-600x253.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-760x320.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-83x35.png 83w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-119x50.png 119w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-740x312.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-220x93.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/I_ve-Abandoned-My-Cart-385x162.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px" /></figure></div>



<p>According to <a href="https://baymard.com/checkout-usability" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">a recent report by Baymard Institute</a>, 69% of all e-commerce visitors abandon their shopping cart with 61% of visitors citing shipping costs as their number one reason:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="655" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-1024x655.png" alt="Reasons for Abandonments During Checkout" class="wp-image-91984" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-1024x655.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-300x192.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-768x491.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-380x243.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-600x384.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-760x486.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-55x35.png 55w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-78x50.png 78w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-740x473.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-220x141.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout-385x246.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Reasons-for-Abandonments-During-Checkout.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/beardbrand-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Beardbrand</a>, a men’s grooming brand, turn cart abandoners into customers by addressing the above objection—shipping costs—and overcoming it in a <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/abandoned-cart-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cart recovery email</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="930" height="540" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email.png" alt="Beardbrand Cart Abandonment Email" class="wp-image-91912" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email.png 930w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-300x174.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-768x446.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-380x221.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-600x348.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-760x441.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-60x35.png 60w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-86x50.png 86w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-740x430.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-220x128.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Cart-Abandonment-Email-385x224.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you know the lifetime value of a customer, as Beardbrand likely does, you can afford to offer discounts to incentivize cart completion.</p>



<p>I know what you’re thinking:</p>



<p><em>“But what if your margins are too thin to compete on shipping?”</em></p>



<p>The answer is simple: <em>ask for feedback.</em></p>



<p>That’s exactly what <a href="https://shop.ugmonk.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Ugmonk</a> does.</p>



<p>After abandoning my cart, I received this email a few hours later:&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="785" height="340" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email.png" alt="Ugmonk Cart Recovery Email" class="wp-image-91992" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email.png 785w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-300x130.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-768x333.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-380x165.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-600x260.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-760x329.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-81x35.png 81w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-115x50.png 115w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-740x321.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-220x95.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ugmonk-Cart-Recovery-Email-385x167.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 785px) 100vw, 785px" /></figure></div>



<p>You can’t always convert abandoning shoppers. That’s a given. But you can make an effort to learn why they didn’t complete their order. Then, learning from that feedback, you can improve your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/checkout-optimization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">checkout process</a> for future customers.</p>


<div id="editors-note-block_5f8857e41d0f7" class="block-editors-note">
    <h3>Editor&#8217;s Note</h3>
    <div><p>We all know that using a <a href="https://sleeknote.com/shopify-popup" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Shopify popup</a> is a great way of recovering lost sales. But did you know you can also show them based on basket size? Well, you can. And with Sleeknote’s <a href="https://sleeknote.com/features/sitedata?ref=e-commerce-email-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">SiteData</a> condition, it’s never been easier. (To learn more about how to create a high-converting popup, <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/popup-statistics" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">read this article</a>.)</p>
