<h2 id="7"><strong>7. The Order Confirmation Email</strong></h2>



<p>After analyzing 100,000+ email receipts, <a href="https://conversio.com/blog/email-receipts-infographic/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Conversio</a> made an interesting discovery:&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Every order confirmation email earns e-commerce stores $0.25 of extra revenue:</strong></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="434" height="432" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt.png" alt="Average Value of Receipt" class="wp-image-91908" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt.png 434w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-300x300.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-150x150.png 150w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-380x378.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-35x35.png 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-50x50.png 50w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-220x219.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-385x383.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Average-Value-of-Receipt-120x120.png 120w" sizes="(max-width: 434px) 100vw, 434px" /></figure></div>



<p>Doesn’t sound like much, right? I didn’t think so, either. But then I looked at the math: <em>For every 100 receipts you send, you can make an average of $25 of extra revenue with no extra effort.</em></p>



<p>Not bad for an automated email, right?</p>



<p>While the order confirmation email is another way to boost sales, it’s also a way of setting customer expectations.</p>



<p><a href="https://joybird.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Joybird</a>, an online furniture store, include an explainer video in their <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/order-confirmation-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">order confirmation email</a> to explain their delivery process:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="790" height="415" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery.png" alt="What to Expect from Delivery" class="wp-image-91996" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery.png 790w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-300x158.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-768x403.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-380x200.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-600x315.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-760x399.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-67x35.png 67w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-95x50.png 95w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-740x389.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-220x116.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/What-to-Expect-from-Delivery-385x202.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 790px) 100vw, 790px" /></figure></div>



<p>Remember, your order confirmation email is more than a digital receipt; it’s also a way of reminding shoppers that buying from you was the right decision.&nbsp;</p>





<h2 id="8"><strong>8. The Upsell Email</strong></h2>



<p>You’re likely familiar with upselling and its close relative, cross-selling.</p>



<p>If you’re not, here’s a refresher:</p>



<ul><li>Upselling is when you invite a prospect to buy a more expensive item in a bid to boost their <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/average-order-value" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">average order value</a>.</li></ul>



<ul><li>Cross-selling involves recommending a related or complementary product.</li></ul>



<p>It’s why McDonald’s asks, “Do you want fries with that?” and why Amazon shows you products that are often bought together:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="780" height="325" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together.png" alt="Amazon Frequently Purchased Together" class="wp-image-91900" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together.png 780w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-300x125.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-768x320.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-380x158.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-600x250.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-760x317.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-84x35.png 84w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-120x50.png 120w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-740x308.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-220x92.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Amazon-Frequently-Purchased-Together-385x160.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" /></figure></div>



<p>With the average <a href="http://www.bain.com/Images/Value_online_customer_loyalty_you_capture.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">repeat customer spending 67 percent more</a> in months 31-36 of his or her shopping relationship than in months zero-to-six, it’s no surprise that many e-commerce brands regularly upsell products to customers who have already made a purchase.</p>



<p>After receiving an order, Beardbrand emails new customers recommended items:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="595" height="385" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email.png" alt="Beardbrand Upsell Email" class="wp-image-91916" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email.png 595w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-300x194.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-400x260.png 400w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-380x246.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-54x35.png 54w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-77x50.png 77w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-220x142.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Upsell-Email-385x249.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" /></figure></div>



<p>If cross-selling isn’t a viable option for you, considering using tiered-pricing.&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/success-stories/apuls" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Apuls</a>, an online retailer specializing in exercise equipment, invites visitors to spend more by offering a value ladder in one of their popups.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="693" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-1024x693.png" alt="Apuls Increase Product Sales Popup" class="wp-image-91904" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-1024x693.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-300x203.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-768x520.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-380x257.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-600x406.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-760x514.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-52x35.png 52w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-74x50.png 74w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-724x490.png 724w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-220x149.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup-385x261.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Apuls-Increase-Product-Sales-Popup.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>From left to right, the item they offer, an exercise bike, increases in price, giving visitors more choice and Apuls a chance to make more from each customer.</p>





<h2 id="9"><strong>9. The Win-Back Email</strong></h2>



<p>It’s happened to me and it’s likely happened to you, too.</p>



<p>You invest your time, attention, and energy in <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/list-building-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">growing your email list</a> only to have a percentage of your readers unsubscribe, or worse, disengage entirely (costing you money in the process).</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="810" height="614" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers.png" alt="Pepperidge Farm Remembers" class="wp-image-91980" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers.png 810w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-300x227.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-768x582.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-380x288.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-600x455.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-760x576.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-46x35.png 46w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-66x50.png 66w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-646x490.png 646w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-220x167.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Pepperidge-Farm-Remembers-385x292.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px" /></figure></div>



<p>Email marketing databases naturally <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/database-decay" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">degrade by about 22.5% every year</a>. So, with that in mind, it’s crucial you re-engage members who have emotionally “checked out” (especially if you want to <a href="http://www.sleeknote.com/blog/reduce-email-unsubscribe-rates" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">reduce email unsubscribe rates</a>).&nbsp;</p>



<p>After moving from <a href="https://us.fotolia.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Fotolia</a> to a competitor (sorry, Fotolia) and ignoring their emails for a few weeks, I received the below email, inviting me back:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="590" height="450" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email.png" alt="Folio Win-Back Email" class="wp-image-91956" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email.png 590w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-300x229.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-380x290.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-46x35.png 46w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-66x50.png 66w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-220x168.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Folio-Win-Back-Email-385x294.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" /></figure></div>



<p>It doesn’t always work (again, sorry Fotolia) but it’s always worth reminding previous buyers you’re still thinking of them (even if they’ve switched to a competitor).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>





<h2 id="10"><strong>10. The Survey Email</strong></h2>



<p>If you don’t ask…</p>



<p>(Say it with me now&#8230;)</p>



<p>You don’t get.</p>



<p>Similarly, if you don’t regularly ask your subscribers what they’re looking for, how can you expect to give them what they want?</p>



<p>Surveying your customers does more than offer valuable insights into their goals, desires and pain points; it gives you an opportunity to improve your email marketing.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Many brands, like <a href="http://www.thefryecompany.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Frye</a>, offer recipients a chance to win a gift certificate if they participate:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="619" height="366" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email.png" alt="Frye Survey Email" class="wp-image-91960" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email.png 619w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-300x177.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-380x225.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-600x355.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-59x35.png 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-85x50.png 85w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-220x130.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Frye-Survey-Email-385x228.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px" /></figure></div>



<p>Others, like The Ask Method Company, founded by survey expert Ryan Levesque, argue otherwise.&nbsp;</p>



<p><em>“If you include a free gift for taking the survey, your data will be biased toward people who just want the free thing,” writes Levesque in his #1 national bestseller, Ask. “If you do want to offer some individual incentive to increase your survey uptake, that incentive should be a discount off the paid solution to their problem in exchange for their feedback.</em></p>



<p><a href="https://www.revolutiontea.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Revolution Tea</a> follows Levesque’s advice to a tee (no pun intended) by offering a discount to users <em>after</em> they completed their survey:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="595" height="405" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email.png" alt="Revolution Tea Survey Email" class="wp-image-91988" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email.png 595w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-300x204.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-380x259.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-51x35.png 51w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-73x50.png 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-220x150.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Revolution-Tea-Survey-Email-385x262.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" /></figure></div>



<p>Asking what your customers want works for many brands, and it can work for yours, too.</p>





<h2 id="11"><strong>11. The Thank You Email</strong></h2>



<p>Sometimes, we don’t say thank you enough. And even if we do, rarely do we <em>really</em> mean it.</p>



<p>Thanking your audience goes beyond thanking them for subscribing to your newsletter or making a purchase; it’s about recognizing they are the reason why you’re in business.</p>



<p>It’s why, once in a while, companies like Brooklinen will write from the heart and thank their customers for helping make what they do possible:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="855" height="555" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email.png" alt="Brooklinen Thank You Email" class="wp-image-91936" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email.png 855w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-300x195.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-768x499.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-400x260.png 400w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-380x247.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-600x389.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-760x493.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-54x35.png 54w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-77x50.png 77w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-740x480.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-220x143.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Brooklinen-Thank-You-Email-385x250.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px" /></figure></div>



<p>It’s easy to get caught up in the minutiae of everyday business life. But sometimes, thanking your customers goes a long way.</p>



<p>How can you give back to the people who’ve made you are your company what it is today?</p>


