<h2><strong>E-Commerce Copywriting Made Simple: How to Write Good Product Descriptions</strong></h2>



<p>If you’re like most e-tailers, you’re using <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-email-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">email marketing</a> to convert subscribers into customers (and customers into repeat customers).</p>



<p>But email marketing isn’t the only channel for conversions.</p>



<p>Often, good product copy is enough (especially for prospects further along <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/the-buyers-journey" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">the buyer’s journey</a>.)</p>



<p>Below, I’ve outlined five foundational copywriting practices that will help you improve your bottom line while nurturing a better relationship with your potential buyers.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Click a link to jump to a particular section:</p>



<p><a href="#1">1. Know Who You’re Writing For</a></p>



<p><a href="#2">2. Harness the Power of Brand Storytelling</a></p>



<p><a href="#3">3. Write Magnetic Headlines</a></p>



<p><a href="#4">4. Use Adjectives Sparingly and Verbs Frequently</a></p>



<p><a href="#5">5. Focus on Benefits Over Features</a></p>



<p>Let’s take a closer look.</p>





<h2 id="1"><strong>1. Know Who You’re Writing For</strong></h2>



<p>In order to know <em>how</em> to write compelling copy, you need to know <em>who</em> you’re writing for.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Once you know who you’re serving, your company’s personality (and, if need be, humor) will naturally render your copy.</p>



<p>A company who understands their ideal buyer is <a href="https://barkbox.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Barkbox</a>.</p>



<p>Using phrases like, “Barkbox is like the joy of a million belly scratches,” and “When your dog falls in ruv with something from the box,” Barkbox write in a way that resonates with their target market: canine enthusiasts.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1010" height="205" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page.png" alt="Barkbox About Page" class="wp-image-92683" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page.png 1010w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-300x61.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-768x156.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-380x77.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-600x122.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-760x154.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-172x35.png 172w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-246x50.png 246w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-740x150.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-220x45.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Barkbox-About-Page-385x78.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 1010px) 100vw, 1010px" /></figure></div>



<p>Puns, spoonerisms and other obscure words that only your ideal buyer would understand is a powerful way to position your product&#8230;</p>



<p>And it’s never been easier to research.</p>



<p>Sites like <a href="https://www.quora.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Quora</a> and <a href="https://www.reddit.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Reddit</a> not only offer insight into your target market’s goals and obstacles, they also reveal <em>how</em> they communicate them to others.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Let’s say you’re an e-tailer specializing in men’s grooming.</p>



<p>One way to write copy that resonates with your ideal buyer would be to browse a subreddit related to your keyword.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/AskMen/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">r/askmen</a>, for example, is a popular subreddit where men ask other men questions:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-1024x504.png" alt="r_askmen" class="wp-image-92731" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-600x295.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Here’s what I found when I researched “shaving”:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="425" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-1024x425.png" alt="_r_askmen Search" class="wp-image-92675" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-1024x425.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-300x124.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-768x319.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-380x158.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-600x249.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-760x315.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-84x35.png 84w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-121x50.png 121w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-740x307.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-220x91.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search-385x160.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/r_askmen-Search.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>As suggested above, a common obstacle for many men when shaving is cutting oneself or irritating one’s skin.</p>



<p>So, if one of your products is a razor, you might use this newfound information to overcome the objection of, “Will it irritate my skin?” in your product description.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.dollarshaveclub.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dollar Shave Club</a> incorporates humor in their product description to handle this very objection. Note the closing sentence below:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="185" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-1024x185.png" alt="Dollar Shave Club Product Description" class="wp-image-92699" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-1024x185.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-300x54.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-768x139.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-380x69.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-600x109.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-760x137.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-180x33.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-250x45.png 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-740x134.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-220x40.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description-385x70.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Dollar-Shave-Club-Product-Description.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you’re on the frontline, fighting your ideal buyer’s objections with them, arm in arm, communicating in a way that’s familiar, your copy will practically write itself.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>





<h2 id="2"><strong>2. Harness the Power of Brand Storytelling</strong></h2>



<p>“As far back as I can remember, I always wanted to be a gangster&#8230;”</p>



<p>“I was 12 going on 13 the first time I saw a dead human being&#8230;”</p>



<p>“People are always asking me if I know Tyler Durden&#8230;”</p>



<p>What do the above have in common?</p>



<p><em>They’re all examples of memorable opening lines.&nbsp;</em></p>



<p>Narratives do more than entertain us; <a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0001128" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">they move us, emotionally</a> (often to the point of action).</p>



<p>They’re why businesses <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-testimonials" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">weave stories into customer testimonials</a> and how companies like <a href="https://www.jackdaniels.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Jack Daniels</a> have popularized their brand with story-driven ads:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="610" height="640" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad.png" alt="Jack Daniels Storytelling Ad" class="wp-image-92727" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad.png 610w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-286x300.png 286w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-380x399.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-600x630.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-33x35.png 33w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-48x50.png 48w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-467x490.png 467w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-220x231.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Jack-Daniels-Storytelling-Ad-385x404.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.pinterest.se/pin/141370875774597748/" target="_blank">Pinterest</a></em></p>





<p>Compelling copy, in <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/product-descriptions" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">product descriptions</a> or otherwise, paints a picture of how the reader’s life will be different if they take the desired action (read: make a purchase). “Here’s where you are, now; here’s where you will be when you take action.”&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="http://www.thinkgeek.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">ThinkGeek</a>, goes one step further, combining humor, pop culture references and <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/story-based-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">storytelling</a> to create visceral imagery in the prospect’s mind:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="810" height="335" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description.png" alt="Think Geek Product Description" class="wp-image-92751" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description.png 810w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-300x124.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-768x318.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-380x157.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-600x248.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-760x314.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-85x35.png 85w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-121x50.png 121w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-740x306.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-220x91.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Think-Geek-Product-Description-385x159.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px" /></figure></div>



<p>While combining storytelling with product descriptions is effective in its own right, it’s amplified even further when reflected on your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-about-page" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">about page</a>.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.harrys.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Harry’s</a> summarize who they are, who they’re for, and why they do what they do on their about page:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="431" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-1024x431.png" alt="Harry_s About Page" class="wp-image-92723" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-1024x431.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-300x126.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-768x323.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-380x160.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-600x252.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-760x320.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-83x35.png 83w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-119x50.png 119w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-740x311.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-220x93.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page-385x162.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Harry_s-About-Page.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Copy like the above does more than assure visitors they’re in the right place; it reminds them the founders are people, too. They encountered a similar problem the visitor has … and decided to do something about it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>To paraphrase Simon Sinek, informing, educating and influencing your ideal buyer doesn’t come from <em>what</em> you do (the product or service you offer); it comes from <em>why</em> you do it.</p>



<p>And there’s no better way to do that than tell a story.</p>





<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Write Magnetic Headlines</strong></h2>



<p>David Ogilvy is one of the greatest copywriters of all time.</p>



<p>He’s also known for prioritizing his headlines above anything else he wrote.</p>



<p>In his own words,</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-style-large"><p><span class="has-inline-color has-plum-color">On the average, five times as many people read the headline as read the body copy. When you have written your headline, you have spent eighty cents out of your dollar.</span></p></blockquote>



<p>Ogilvy was famous for writing twenty headlines for each ad he wrote for this very reason.&nbsp;</p>



<p>And although you don’t have to emulate Ogilvy (though it might help), you <em>do</em> need to think about what you’re trying to communicate in your product description headlines.</p>



<p><a href="http://www.copyblogger.com/magnetic-headlines/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">According to Copyblogger</a>, 8 out of 10 people will read your headline copy, but only 2 out of 10 will read the rest. And those who do, have <a href="http://www.statisticbrain.com/attention-span-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">an attention span of 8.25 seconds</a>.</p>



<p>With that in mind, writing magnetic headlines from the offset is more important than ever.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>While good headline writing goes beyond this article, there are a few things you can do to quickly and easily improve their effectiveness:</p>



<p>One way to do that is to incorporate one or more of <a href="https://www.quicksprout.com/the-definitive-guide-to-copywriting-chapter-3/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">the four U’s</a> in your headline writing.</p>



<p>Here’s a brief overview:</p>





<p><strong>i. Unique</strong></p>



<p>If you want to rise above the fray in today’s noisy online marketplace, you need to differentiate yourself from your competitors.</p>



<p>And there’s no better way than having a unique angle or value proposition in your headline.</p>



<p>Take a look at the two examples below.</p>



<p>Which piques your interest more?</p>



<p>Example A&#8230;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="560" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-1024x560.png" alt="Bar Hill Tom Cat Gin" class="wp-image-92679" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-1024x560.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-300x164.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-768x420.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-380x208.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-600x328.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-760x415.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-64x35.png 64w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-92x50.png 92w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-740x404.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-220x120.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin-385x210.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bar-Hill-Tom-Cat-Gin.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>&#8230;or, Example B?</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="560" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-1024x560.png" alt="Unicorn Tears Gin Liqueur" class="wp-image-92755" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-1024x560.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-300x164.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-768x420.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-380x208.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-600x328.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-760x415.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-64x35.png 64w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-92x50.png 92w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-740x404.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-220x120.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur-385x210.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Unicorn-Tears-Gin-Liqueur.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>If you’re not a gin connoisseur or concerned with price, you probably chose Example B.</p>



<p>Why?</p>



<p><em>Because it’s highly unique.</em></p>



<p>Product description like the above is common for <a href="https://www.firebox.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Firebox</a>. They’re funny, unique and attract a ton of free press because of it:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="580" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-1024x580.png" alt="Firebox Press" class="wp-image-92719" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-1024x580.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-300x170.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-768x435.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-380x215.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-600x340.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-760x431.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-62x35.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-88x50.png 88w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-740x419.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-220x125.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press-385x218.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Firebox-Press.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>It’s important to mention here, copy like the above is consistent with Firebox’s voice. They know exactly who their market is and who they’re writing for (by their own admission they’re “Not for everyone”).&nbsp;</p>



<p>This is why knowing who you’re writing for is crucial. The greater your understanding of your audience, the more you can differentiate yourself with your copy.</p>





<p><strong>ii. Ultra-specific</strong></p>



<p>Specificity is a key element of writing magnetic headlines.</p>



<p>And although it can pertain to numbers (<a href="https://moz.com/blog/5-data-insights-into-the-headlines-readers-click" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">numbers in headlines are known to generate 73% more social shares and engagement</a>), it’s most effective when it demonstrates who your brand is for (and equally, not for).&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="https://www.fiftythree.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">FiftyThree</a> specifies exactly who their ideal buyer is in their headline (spoiler alert: it’s everyone):</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="635" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-1024x635.png" alt="FiftyThree Headline" class="wp-image-92715" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-1024x635.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-300x186.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-768x476.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-380x236.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-600x372.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-760x471.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-56x35.png 56w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-81x50.png 81w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-740x459.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-220x136.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline-385x239.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FiftyThree-Headline.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Visitors need to know, immediately, whether they’re in the right place and whether what you’re offering is relevant to their needs and interests.</p>



<p>And if they know they are, they’re more likely to read your product copy (and hopefully make a purchase).</p>





<p><strong>iii. Urgent</strong></p>



<p>You probably already know <a href="https://conversionxl.com/research-study/urgency-ecommerce-product-page/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">urgency increases e-commerce conversions</a>.</p>



<p>Why?</p>



<p><em>Because it forces consumers to make a decision.</em></p>



<p>The <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/fomo-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">fear of missing out</a> (FOMO) is a <em>real</em> concern for most people.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2016/03/160330135623.htm" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">And the science proves it</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="http://sockbox.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Sockbox</a> uses urgency in their headline to nudge prospects off the fence and make a purchase before the month’s shipment goes out:&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="575" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-1024x575.png" alt="Sockbox" class="wp-image-92739" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-1024x575.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-300x169.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-768x432.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-380x214.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-600x337.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-760x427.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-62x35.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-89x50.png 89w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-740x416.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-220x124.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox-385x216.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sockbox.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>You don’t always have to rely on urgency to move potential buyers to action…</p>



<p>But it might help.</p>





<p><strong>iv. Useful</strong></p>



<p><a href="http://journals.ama.org/doi/abs/10.1509/jmr.10.0353?code=amma-site" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">In a study of 7,000 <em>New York Times</em> articles</a>, Jonah Berger found <em>useful</em> content is more likely to go viral.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>In his own words,</p>



<p>“Practically useful content may be more viral because it provides information.”</p>



<p>Makes sense, right? The more information a prospect has, the easier it is to make a purchasing decision.</p>



<p>It’s no surprise, then, many e-tailers focus on <em>useful</em> headlines for their product descriptions.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.crateandbarrel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Crate and Barrel</a> write helpful headlines by asking the visitor which lighting fixture best meets their preference:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="560" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-1024x560.png" alt="Crate and Barrel" class="wp-image-92695" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-1024x560.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-300x164.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-768x420.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-380x208.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-600x328.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-760x415.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-64x35.png 64w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-92x50.png 92w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-740x404.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-220x120.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel-385x210.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Crate-and-Barrel.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you combine one or more of the four Us, your headlines will attract attention and your readers will naturally move on to read your product copy.&nbsp;</p>





<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Use Adjectives Sparingly and Verbs Frequently</strong></h2>



<p>If you’re anything like me, your high school creative writing assignments can be summarized by one recurring remark:</p>



<p>“Needs more adjectives.”</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="610" height="455" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell.png" alt="Christopher Walken Need More Cowbell" class="wp-image-92691" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell.png 610w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-300x224.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-380x283.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-600x448.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-47x35.png 47w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-67x50.png 67w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-220x164.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Christopher-Walken-Need-More-Cowbell-385x287.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></figure></div>



<p>But we’re not writing to entertain.</p>



<p>We’re writing to <em>sell</em>.</p>



<p>And that means using fewer adjectives and more verbs.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970203833004577251490098811270" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">an analysis of college </a>applications, Dee Leopold, managing director of admissions for Harvard Business School, found applications that included verbs were more likely to be accepted than those that favored adjectives.</p>



<p>Similarly, when writing product copy, verbs outperform adjectives because they <em>help move the reader toward the desired result</em>.</p>



<p>Take a look at the below example from <a href="https://www.crowdcontent.com/resources/writer/university/e-commerce/action-verbs-and-sensory-adjectives/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Crowd Content</a>.</p>



<p>Which, in your opinion, is more persuasive?</p>



<p>“This beautiful necklace is perfect for your fashionable tastes.”&nbsp;</p>



<p>Or,</p>



<p>“This necklace will satisfy the desires of the fashionista in you.”&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>The former describes the product, but the latter addresses the needs of the buyer.</p>



<p>Much more effective, right?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>If you insist on including adjectives in your copy, you need to make them count.</p>



<p>One way to do that is to include <em>sensory </em>adjectives in your copy.</p>



<p>When combined with storytelling, sensory adjectives help the reader visualize what they’re reading about and encourages them to invest in the product further.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.blueapron.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Blue Apron</a> rely on sensory adjectives like “juicy” and “flavorful” to entice readers to try their menus:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="685" height="585" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description.png" alt="Blue Apron Product Description" class="wp-image-92687" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description.png 685w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-300x256.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-380x325.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-600x512.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-41x35.png 41w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-59x50.png 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-574x490.png 574w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-220x188.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Blue-Apron-Product-Description-385x329.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 685px) 100vw, 685px" /></figure></div>



<p>As you can probably imagine, future pacing the desired result can evoke strong emotions in the reader.</p>



<p>But emotion on its own isn’t enough to motivate the reader to take action.You need to <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-testimonials" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>lead them by the hand and take them exactly where to go</em></a><em> </em>(ht: Gary Halbert).</p>



<p>And there’s no better way to do that than in your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/write-powerful-cta" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">call-to-action</a> (CTA).</p>



<p>While having “Add to cart” copy is a no-brainer for most e-tailers, there’s no harm in having a CTA in your product description, too.</p>



<p><a href="https://scoutbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">ScoutBooks</a> outline exactly what they want their visitors to do in the product descriptions, step-by-step:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="610" height="120" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books.png" alt="Scout Books" class="wp-image-92735" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books.png 610w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-300x59.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-380x75.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-600x118.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-180x35.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-250x50.png 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-220x43.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Scout-Books-385x76.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></figure></div>



<p>The more instruction you give the reader, the easier it is for them to know what to do (and the faster you can turn casual visitors into paying customers).</p>



<p>Listen to Joanna Wiebe discuss this below:</p>



<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jrSrg6tT4MQ?start=551" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>





<h2 id="5"><strong>5. Focus on Benefits Over Features</strong></h2>



<p>It’s a classic scene.</p>



<p>You’re interviewing for a job and the employer utters four words candidates pray they won’t hear:&nbsp;</p>



<p><em>Sell me this pen.</em></p>



<p>If it’s happened to you, chances are, one of two things happened next:</p>



<p>You explained the pen’s <em>features, </em>what it is or does, its color, its weight, etc.</p>



<p>Or, you outlined the <em>benefits</em> of owning the pen. Specifically, how it would improve the owner’s life.</p>



<p>The truth is, while it’s tempting to wax on about a product’s ins-and-outs, most people don’t care about what your product <em>is </em>or <em>does</em>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Rather, they care about how what you’re offering can help them bridge the gap between where they are now and where they want to be.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>



<p>As <a href="http://rayedwards.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Ray Edwards</a> says, “Everyone’s favorite FM radio station is WIIFM: what’s in it for me?”</p>



<p>A good rule of thumb to follow when writing product descriptions, then, is to tie a benefit to every feature you write.</p>



<p>Notice how <a href="https://www.intelligentchange.com/products/the-five-minute-journal" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Intelligent Change</a>, in the below example, focus on the after effect of buying The Five-Minute Journal:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="610" height="275" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description.png" alt="The Five-Minute Journal Product Description" class="wp-image-92747" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description.png 610w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-300x135.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-380x171.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-600x270.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-78x35.png 78w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-111x50.png 111w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-220x99.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/The-Five-Minute-Journal-Product-Description-385x174.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></figure></div>



<p>There’s no mention of the material the journal’s made from or the paper it’s printed on … all that matters is how it will improve the buyer’s life.</p>



<p>Depending on your page’s layout, benefits can be written in the copy itself (like above) or using bullet points.&nbsp;</p>



<p>If it’s the latter, your bullets will often be organized using an information hierarchy, with the most persuasive bullets at the top and bottom, with general benefits in-between.</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.amazon.com/T-fal-Nonstick-Thermo-Spot-Dishwasher-Cookware/dp/B00WM3IQ54/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">T-Fal</a> promoting their non-stick frying pan.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="660" height="120" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description.png" alt="T-Fal Product Description" class="wp-image-92743" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description.png 660w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-300x55.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-380x69.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-600x109.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-180x33.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-250x45.png 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-220x40.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/T-Fal-Product-Description-385x70.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you combine best practices such as playful humor, brand storytelling, and benefit-driven copy, your product descriptions will evoke more emotion in your ideal buyer—and your bottom line will reflect it.&nbsp;</p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e6b6231abd15" class="block-content-upgrade">
